      • inFormat

        public FlowProcessor inFormat(org.apache.camel.spi.DataFormat inFormat)
        Sets the DataFormat to be applied to the Exchange.getIn() message body for creating a byte array representation. The original message body is not replaced by the byte array. The data format is only applied during createPacket(org.apache.camel.Exchange) calls. Calls to this method are made by the PlatformMessage.createPacket() method on messages created by this processor.
        Parameters:
        inFormat - a data formatting strategy.
        Returns:
        this processor.

      • outFormat

        public FlowProcessor outFormat(org.apache.camel.spi.DataFormat outFormat)
        Sets the DataFormat to be applied to a message body's byte array representation for creating the Exchange.getIn() message body (replacing the original message body). The outFormat is applied:
        • if outConversion(boolean) is set to true, during createPacket(org.apache.camel.Exchange) calls, made by PlatformMessage.createPacket()
        • during createExchange(PlatformPacket) calls, made by FlowBeginProcessor.replay(PlatformPacket))
        If both outFormat(DataFormat) and outType(Class) are set, outType is ignored and only outFormat is used.
        Parameters:
        outFormat - a data formatting strategy.
        Returns:
        this processor.

      • inType

        public FlowProcessor inType(Class<?> inType)
        Sets the data type the Exchange.getIn() message body shall be converted to (replacing the original message body) before creating the internal byte array representation. The conversion is only made during createPacket(org.apache.camel.Exchange) calls. Calls to this method are made by the PlatformMessage.createPacket() method on messages created by this processor.
        Parameters:
        inType - type of the Exchange.getIn() message's body that replaces the original message body.
        Returns:
        this processor.

      • outType

        public FlowProcessor outType(Class<?> outType)
        Sets the data type the Exchange.getIn() message body shall be converted to (replacing the original message body) from the internal byte array representation. The conversion is made:
        • if outConversion(boolean) is set to true, during createPacket(org.apache.camel.Exchange) calls, made by PlatformMessage.createPacket()
        • during createExchange(PlatformPacket) calls, made by FlowBeginProcessor.replay(PlatformPacket))
        Parameters:
        outType - type of the Exchange.getIn() message's body that replaces the original message body.
        Returns:
        this processor.

      • outConversion

        public FlowProcessor outConversion(boolean outConversion)
        Set to false to skip conversion of outgoing message bodies. This is recommended to improve performance when using re-readable message bodies. This setting is ignored when re-playing messages.
        Parameters:
        outConversion - false to skip conversion of outgoing message bodies. Default is true.
        Returns:
        this processor.
        See Also:
        FlowBeginProcessor.replay(PlatformPacket)

      • createPacket

        public PlatformPacket createPacket(org.apache.camel.Exchange exchange)
        Creates a PlatformPacket from an exchange applying either native type conversion to byte array or using inFormat(DataFormat) (higher priority). If outConversion is false no further conversion of the body of the Exchange.getIn() message is done, otherwise, outFormat or outType are applied. If both are not set a conversion to InputStream type is made.
        Specified by:
        createPacket in interface PlatformPacketFactory
        Parameters:
        exchange - message exchange.
        Returns:
        a new PlatformPacket.
